---

**Root cause of the new error: `max_output_tokens = 8192` was too small**

A full company profile with 5+ items across 4 arrays (problems, differentiators, complaints, moves) easily generates **15,000–25,000 tokens**. The model was generating real, correct data — but the API hard-cut it at 8,192 tokens mid-JSON, before the closing `}` could be written. That's why you saw `"no '}' found"` consistently across all 3 retries (same truncation point every time).

**Fix 1 — `MAX_OUTPUT_TOKENS = 65536`** (was 8192). `gemini-2.5-flash` supports up to 65k output tokens. This alone should make 95% of failures disappear.

---

**Fix 2 — AI repair pass** (for the remaining edge cases)

When a parse still fails after increasing the token limit, instead of just retrying the same expensive Google Search call 3 times, the script now:

1. **Saves the raw response** to `data/raw/company_model_attempt1.txt` — so no data is ever lost, even from a truncated response
2. **Runs a repair call** using `gemini-2.5-flash-lite` with NO Google Search — it just reads whatever partial text was saved and restructures it into valid JSON. This is cheap and fast since it's not doing any research, just reformatting

